toshi reagon and biglovely toshi reagon and biglovely facebook twitter email print add to calendar singer songwriter toshi reagon has a musical personality equally at home on a formal concert stage or in a rowdy blues bar atlanta born and brooklyn based reagon effortlessly moves among traditional african american folk blues and gospel music genres to vintage rock reggae and contemporary pop her voice is by turns earthy and sweet her band biglovely grooves with easy grace and her music nests sharp social commentary in sensual vocal harmonies with infectious hooks as reagon told acoustic guitar magazine growing up there wasn t anything i couldn t listen to in my house ever to me my musical taste is not eclectic just very wide and i know it sounds hokey but i really see a oneness in music reagon collaborates frequently with her mother bernice johnson reagon founder of the gospel a cappella group sweet honey in the rock and has performed alongside fellow songwriters elvis costello lenny kravitz chaka kahn and ani difranco among others her discography as a leader extends from the time honored smithsonian folkways series 1997 s kindness to difranco s edgy righteous babe records 2005 s have you heard when friday october 29 2010 8 00 pm where dinkelspiel auditorium map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students tags performance music arts sponsor s stanford lively arts contact 650 725 arts 2787 livelyarts stanford edu admission $38.00 42.00 adult $10.00 stanford student other discounts available please check website for more information permalink http events stanford edu events 244 24427 more information last modified october 28 2010
